message.content:
Here's a table of the planets in our solar system, along with their average distance from the Sun in astronomical units (AU) and their mythological significance:

| Planet      | Distance from Sun (AU) | Mythological Significance                                      |
|-------------|------------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------|
| Mercury     | 0.39                   | Named after the Roman messenger god, known for speed and mobility. |
| Venus       | 0.72                   | Named after the Roman goddess of love and beauty.                  |
| Earth       | 1.00                   | The name Earth is derived from Old English and Germanic words meaning "ground." It is not associated with mythology. |
| Mars        | 1.52                   | Named after the Roman god of war.                                   |
| Jupiter     | 5.20                   | Named after the king of the Roman gods, god of sky and thunder.     |
| Saturn      | 9.58                   | Named after the Roman god of agriculture and harvest.               |
| Uranus      | 19.22                  | Named after the Greek god of the sky, father of the Titans.         |
| Neptune     | 30.05                  | Named after the Roman god of the sea.                               |

Note: The distances are average distances from the Sun and can vary slightly due to the elliptical nature of planetary orbits.
